descript.abstract: Boundary of the County of Napa developed using the California Government Code 23128 descriptions.
descript.purpose: To show the extent of the Napa County boundary using the California Government Code 23128 descriptions.
descript.supplinf: California Government Code 23128 were used along with surrounding county boundary codes 23117 (Lake County), 23148 (Solano County), and 23149 (Sonoma County)

procstep.procdesc: Received the California Government Code sections from Public Works. The majority of the county boundary follows the ridgelines. The 5ft and 10ft elevation and hillshading data was used to delineate the ridgeline. In areas where the ridgeline was not used as a boundary we used the record of surveys and the metes and bounds to determine where the boundary was.
